summary: Completed comprehensive frontend testing of My Coach Developer iPad coach observation app. All core features working correctly including session creation, live observation with 3-column grid, timer system, ball rolling toggle, session parts, event logging with descriptors, undo functionality, session review with metrics/charts, and template management.
passed_tests: Home page loads with correct title and create session card
Session setup page with name input, template selector, event types, descriptors, session parts
Live observation 3-column grid (Events yellow, Content Focus blue, Delivery Method green)
Timer starts and runs correctly during observation
Ball rolling toggle works and shows correct state (orange when rolling, gray when stopped)
Session part tabs allow switching between Warm Up, Practice, Game, Reflection
Event logging with yellow buttons creates events with toast feedback
Descriptor buttons activate after event selection and can be toggled
Undo button removes last event correctly
Session completion navigates to review page
Review page shows summary with metrics (duration, events, ball rolling %)
View toggle between whole session and session parts
Template management page allows creating, duplicating templates
PDF and CSV export buttons present and accessible
iPad-friendly UI with large touch targets and clear visual feedback
